
Through conda:
$ conda install --name ELT-2-ChIP --file ELT-2-ChIP.env.linux-64.txt
$ conda activate ELT-2-ChIP

Notes:

SPP:
It is an R package, but the authors have written a wrapper script: run_spp.R from https://github.com/kundajelab/phantompeakqualtools

java:
conda install -c anaconda openjdk
